    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Achievements Of the Cardinal</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Chris McLeester letter on May 5 article on death of Cardinal John O'Connor; calls for more equity within church on place of priests and nuns</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>According to your May 5 front-page article ''O'Connor Successor Unclear, but the Challenges Are Not,'' one of the central problems of the New York Archdiocese is a scarcity of priests. You report that there are more than 870 priests in the archdiocese and 3,700 nuns. If the Roman Catholic Church allowed women to be ordained as priests, this problem would not exist.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>According to your May 5 front-page article ''O'Connor Successor Unclear, but the Challenges Are Not,'' one of the central problems of the New York Archdiocese is a scarcity of priests. You report that there are more than 870 priests in the archdiocese and 3,700 nuns. If the Roman Catholic Church allowed women to be ordained as priests, this problem would not exist.</p>
        <p>It is time for the church to change its practice and solve a pressing problem while increasing equality within the church.</p>
        <p>CHRIS MCLEESTER  Philadelphia, May 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
